&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants for April and October 2021 cohorts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is a world renowned centre specialising in heart and lung disease. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re looking for newly qualified or experienced band 5 nurses who are ambitious and inspired by change to join our leading Cardiothoracic Rotation Programme at Harefield Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to developing our staff, which is why we are proud to be offering a bespoke 18-month specialist rotation programme. This involves six-month placements on three of our specialist areas to build up your clinical skills and knowledge and equip you for your future career in Cardiorespiratory nursing. These specialist areas include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiology ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surgical wards (including private patients)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Transplant unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Critical Care units&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our programme is recognised as a leading rotation programme across London and we have showcased our great success at various national conferences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;On each new placement you will have a supernumerary period and an allocated mentor. You will work alongside practice educators, clinical nurse specialists, advance nurse practitioners and other experienced nurses. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a dedicated education supervisor throughout the 18 months who will provide tailor-made professional support, facilitate learning opportunities and help you develop your role in cardiorespiratory nursing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A comprehensive educational programme, with dedicated study days and a preceptorship programme will be provided to support your transition to working within each specialist area. This can help you get a greater understanding of the nurse that you are and the future you want in your career. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Once you have completed the rotation we will give you a guaranteed job in the Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;After the rotation programme, further opportunities are available to enhance your professional career development; such as university modules, MSc pathways and in house clinical education and leadership programmes that will allow you to progress to a Band 6 position. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like any further information, please contact Alexandra Wilson (Sister, Clinical Education) on 01895823737 bleep 1449, or email a.wilson@rbht.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
